  "text": "As with all asymmetrical olefins [CITATION_1] the attacking radical will add to the carbon center that will generate the most stable radical intermediate, which in this case is the terminal C-3 carbon center. The radical sum of a general hypofluorite ROF gave the product distributions and reaction mechanisms shown in Scheme 3.",
